Source.Contents:
/#
   A type that describes average rate options rate observations. This is used to describe a parametric frequency of rate observations against a particular rate. Typical frequencies might include daily, every Friday, etc.
 #/
record FpML5.confirmation.FxAverageRateObservationSchedule {
  # The start of the period over which observations are made to determine whether a trigger has occurred.
  startDate : date

  # The end of the period over which observations are made to determine whether a trigger event has occurred.
  endDate : date

  # The frequency at which calculation period end dates occur with the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.
  calculationPeriodFrequency : FpML5.confirmation.CalculationPeriodFrequency

}

startDate.Doc: The start of the period over which observations are made to determine whether a trigger has occurred.
startDate.Name: startDate

endDate.Doc: The end of the period over which observations are made to determine whether a trigger event has occurred.
endDate.Name: endDate

calculationPeriodFrequency.Doc: The frequency at which calculation period end dates occur with the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.
calculationPeriodFrequency.Name: calculationPeriodFrequency
